- VSCode Version: 1.5.1
- OS Version: 10.11.6 (15G1004)

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create an extension that uses `vscode.previewHtml` command to open an URI that is registered to `TextDocumentContentProvider`
2. Generate a document that contains a link to a file URI to a specific line. I've noticed the file needs to be in the current project that is open. If it's not, the bug doesn't appear.
3. The link doesn't work when it has also a line reference, without it it works.

For example I was able to reproduce the issue with the extension below. Execute the command when there's a file open in the project. The URI to the file to a specific line doesn't work, but the URI to the same file without line specified it works.

``` javascript
"use strict";

const vscode = require("vscode");

const scheme = "test-scheme";
const eventEmitter = new vscode.EventEmitter();

const provider = {
    scheme,

    provideTextDocumentContent: function(uri) {
        const file = vscode.window.activeTextEditor.document.uri.toString();
        const urlWithLine = `${ file }#L10`;
        const urlWoLine = `${ file }`;
        return `
<a href="${ urlWithLine }">Link to file with line, doesn't work</a><br/><br/>
<a href="${ urlWoLine }">Link to same file without line, works</a>
`;
    },

    onDidChange: function() {
        return eventEmitter.event;
    },

    update: function(uri) {
        eventEmitter.fire(uri);
    }
};

function exec() {
    const uri = vscode.Uri.parse(`${ scheme }://test/test`);
    vscode.commands.executeCommand("vscode.previewHtml", uri);
}

function activate(context) {
    context.subscriptions.push(vscode.commands.registerCommand("testExt.exec", exec));

    context.subscriptions.push(vscode.workspace.registerTextDocumentContentProvider(scheme, provider));
}

exports.activate = activate;
```

![vscode-bug](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10324676/18810970/879d1388-82ac-11e6-9e65-a252cfdeabb2.gif)

It would be a really nice feature, if the `CompletionItem` can actually return promises as their `additionalTextEdits`.

I'm imaging the following feature:
You are autocompleting something (in my example it's an import that is added to the programmers file) and there are other imports that have the same class name. Now it would be cool if I can add a Promise to the additionalTextEdits to ask the user with a `showInputBox` for an alias name.

Example:

``` typescript
import {Foobar} from 'whatever';

let foo = new Foobar();
```

Now if I autocomplete another `Foobar` class from the library `foobaz`, I want to ask the developer for an aliased name to generate the following code:

``` typescript
import {Foobar} from 'whatever';
import {Foobar as MyFoobar} from 'foobaz';

let foo = new Foobar();
/*...*/
```

To do so, the additionalTextEdit should have the possibility to be a promise like so:

``` typescript
completionItem.additionalTextEdits = [
    vscode.window.showInputBox(/*...*/).then(name => {
        //prepare the text edit with the given name (if any)
        return TextEdit;
});
]
```

What do you guys think?
Cheers

